description: "Night of the Butcher" act 1! He feeds on human flesh, brutally dismembering victims to satisfy his obscene hunger, and he is but the newest nightmare facing the Golden Age Sandman!
name: Night of the Butcher: Act 1 of 4

description: Guest-artist Michael Lark (THE VISITOR, RAY BRADBURY COMICS SPECIAL) illustrates an after-hours odyssey through the turbulent streets of New York City as Shade encounters what may prove to be his strangest nightmare yet.
name: Lunch With Lenny

description: A Wolf in Cheap Clothing, Part 2 of 4. Finding the situation even more volatile than Starfleet had believed, Kirk pulls out the landing party from Zantak Prime.
name: A Wolf...In Cheap Clothing Part Two

description: Part 4 of 4. Commander Riker finds that keeping an old promise has inadvertently led to murder and the creation of a machine that may destroy the very civilization Riker believed he was preserving.
name: The Last Verse

description:
Guest artist Teddy Kristiansen illustrates the first in a series of interspersed one-shot stories delving into Opal City's past, drawn from the diaries of the enigmatic Golden Age villain, The Shade. In the 1880s, Shade brings his perverse brand of justice to play against a circus of the damned...

A cold, winter night finds Jack Knight reading The Shade's Journal...

June 1882, Oscar Wilde is on his American tour. He is enjoying an afternoon with The Shade - also known as "Mr. Black" - at the outdoor Cafe de Salle in Opal City. Mr. Black is approached by one Jason Mayville. Mayville seeks to employ Mr. Black to recover his sister from the thrall of the Pepper Stage Troupe and its leader Lune...
name: 1882 - Back Stage, Back Then: A Tale of Times Past

description:
When Superboy and the Suicide Squad storm the secret headquarters of the criminal organization known as Dragon, they soon realize one of their own may be as traitor. Can the Boy of Steel and his super-villain cohorts survive this well laid death trap?

Team members are dead and the sea is rushing in. Is Superboy going to drown under the ocean? Or just simply be eaten?
name: Water grave part 2 of 3

description:
“River Run” continues: Swamp Thing arrives in an alternative America-one in which the Nazis won World War II, where he is offered the chance to avenge millions of murdered souls.

In the second story of River Run, Twilight of the Gods, Swamp Thing now enters a world where Nazi Germany has taken over the world, and Alois Hitler is married to Norma Jean Baker. Using Jewish occult magic, Swamp Thing is summoned as a golem by the American President, who wants to use the elemental to wipe out the world in a mass genocide, rather then have a world that was born out of the extinction of over a dozen races carry on. But, Swamp Thing points out that one genocide can't make up for another, so the President destroys Swamp Thing's body. But, he didn't dispose of it properly, and the true spirit of justice carries out said genocide.

Note: This chapter is inspired in the earth-x concept from the pre-crisis multiverse.
name: Twilight of the Gods: Chapter Two of River Run

description: The Joker joins with Mrs. Sazia after he threatens her. The Inspector is almost killed while investigating one of Paulie Longo's safe houses where a bunch of Longo's men have been murdered with Joker Venom. Diana saves him. Artemis takes down the runner of  a sweatshop and frees all of the women who are forced to work there. Diana visits Mrs. Sazia but has to go through her two superhuman guards first. Once inside she tries to reason with Mrs. Sazia and explains that the Joker is bad news. The Joker comes out from another room with a bomb strapped to his chest and the timer has 2 seconds left on it.
name: Joker's Holiday

description: Grip and his henchmen attack the armored car and policemen escorting Alica Cordova, and does battle with the Dragon. Grip escapes however, kidnapping Cordova in the process. It is also revealed that agent Sheridan is in cahoots with Grip. The Dragon and Officer Alex Wilde begin their hunt for Grip.

Julie tells Maxx and Sarah about her time while she was missing. This upsets Maxx.

We find the 2 thugs from issue 1 in side by side jail cells. One is sharing the cell with an Is.

The Dragon is badly beaten by the Fiend, who escapes. The Dragon is hospitalized, but then rescues the captive Howard Niseman from the strange Octopus creature, who has been holding Cyberface captive. Overlord prepares for war.

Spawn continues his journey towards New York, but unfortunately is caught in a battle with the klan itself. Spawn attempts to protect one of the last black families in the area, by slowly sabotages the lives of the Klan members.

Before spawn leaves, he finds the Klan leader, and leaves him a little suprise
name: The Clan

description: Winter, Henry Bendix and Cannon confront three M.A.D. units and wonder how they can defeat them. Bendix comes up with an ingenious plan that has his group infiltrate the Russian M.A.D. base, destroying it. Stormwatch finds the whereabouts of the WildC.A.T.S, a team they believe is responsible for the death of Battalion. The two teams confront each other, ready for a huge battle.

Chicago , where the X-Men are standing in the middle of a mob of frightened humans. The people are panicking due to the probes that Holocaust has sent. Sunfire becomes angry and powers up, thus frightening the crowd even more. He flies up to attack the probes, and Rogue chases after him. She makes contact with him and absorbs some of his memories, while Morph wonders what that will do to her mind. We have a flashback to Sunfire being tortured by Nemesis and Apocalypse. They both fall, but Morph manages to catch them before they hit the ground. The X-Men return to their mission of evacuating the humans.

At the Xavier mansion, Magneto is spending a quiet moment alone with his son. Bishop goes to confront him about him staying home while the X-Men risk their lives, but stops when he sees Magneto is with Charles. He apologizes, but Magneto says he should be the one apologizing to his son; if Bishop is right about their world, then Charles will cease to exist. Bishop tries to tell him that their world was created by some kind of cosmic accident, but Magneto tells him that love is never an accident. He tells Bishop that the world may end tomorrow; give him tonight to say goodbye to his son.

Meanwhile, Apocalypse is angry about Abyss' failure to stop the X-Men in Maine(see Amazing X-Men). Rex tells him that they've found the location of the X-Men's secret base: the former residence of Charles Xavier. Apocalypse gloats and tells Rex that he'll be handling this personally.

Back in Chicago, Blink is reluctantly preparing to send Sabretooth and Wild Child to confront Holocaust. Sabretooth is the one who rescued her from Abyss many years ago, and she's worried that he won't be coming back. Rogue flies in and interrupts, telling them to go back and help with the evac. Blink displaces her for a fraction of a second, and then sends Sabretooth to Indianapolis.

Sabretooth rouses Wild Child, and they confront Holocaust. Sabretooth and Holocaust argue about their past together, when Sabretooth used to work for Holocaust. Then Holocaust, quite frankly, makes one of the stupidest moves a villain can make. Since "Sabretooth is going to die anyway",he reveals the location of his secret Infinite processing plant.(Ugh). Anyways, Sabretooth sends Wild Child to tell Rogue, while he and Holocaust battle. During the battle, Holocaust talks about how much he enjoyed killing Magneto's daughter. Creed manages to rip Holocaust's containment helmet off, and then collapses. The issue ends with Holocaust standing over Sabertooth's fallen body.
name: No Exit

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The Black Widow follows a tip received from an old friend. In the Canadian Northwest, a strange energy pulse has alerted the Avengers’ attention. Could the Black Widow’s tip and the peculiar energy readings be connected? Featuring the return of the Red Skull!
name: Evil in a Cold and Lonely Place

description: Without his new armor, Cap would lie paralyzed! With it, he intends to go out in a blaze of glory!
name: The Bombs Bursting in Air
Real Heroes!
Betrayal

description:
Scott Summers has already betrayed his "father", Mr. Sinister.  Is he now plotting against his brother Alex?

The breeding pens has thousands of mutants imprisoned, using the power of four embodied telepath mutants, Sinister managed to sedate them. One single mutant has taking relevance in this new order, Lorna Darne aka Polaris has been for years imprisoned, mentally unbalanced believes she Magneto´s daughter, now she is the only mutant that saw who is helping prisoners to scape from breeding pens.

Sinistes has gone and his trace with him, Apocalypse propose to Cyclops be the new Horseman in the near future, but Havok has something to say and he won´t allow that his brother get this rank without a fight.
name: Abandoned Children

description:
The team teleports to the Shi'ar Empire to retrieve the M'Kraan Crystal but run into the Imperial Guard and the Starjammers. 

Synopsis

Gambit and his X-Ternals land in front of the Imperial Guard on the planet Ch'reesharaa in the Shi'ar Galaxy, courtesy of Lila Cheney's long dormant and suppressed powers of spacial teleportation. The results are not good. Not only does Lila pass out, but Gladiator demands the new arrivals to give themselves up while being backed by twenty or so warriors. Rictor, the Apocalyptic cop, has no problem surrendering. Those following Gambit's lead: scramble. The Imperial Guard chases the fleeing X-Ternals. The first to reach them is Starbolt. Sunspot, who derives his power from solar absorption, easily defeats Starbolt and the chase continues. Gladiator is next to challenge the X-Ternals. He attempts to crush Guido, but Guido simply rechannels the kinetic energy from the hit in order to knock Gladiator out of commission. The team then strategizes to lose their pursuers in a nearby forest.
 
Having reached the forest, Lila awakens. Spirits are low. Suddenly, the plant life in the jungle springs to life and ensnares the X-Ternals. The Imperial Guard catches up but can't find a trace of Gambit's team. Reporting back to Gladiator, the Imperial Guard is upset about the obvious reaction their foibles will get from their superiors. Oracle, however, feels she has an ace up her sleeve. Rictor, having surrendered, promises that he can be used to find the X-Ternals. He has a tracking device planted on one of the X-Ternals and exchanges his services for the promise that he'll be able to take Gambit's squad back to earth to be punished for their Earth crimes.
 
Meanwhile, Gambit begins to charge his throwing knives to free his troop from the plants when he is stopped by a mysterious group. A man tells the X-Ternals that the plant-life is sentient. Lila knows this makes sense because when she opened her portal she felt as if the planet were calling to her. The leader of the group introduces himself as Jonath once the X-Ternals are let down from the foliage. He explains that he and his men were banished after failing to protect the life of their ruler from assassination by its children. The next ruler, D'Ken, found the M'Kraan Crystal, the nexus of all realities. He used its powers to steal the throne from his sister, Deathbird. He then killed his younger sister Lilandra and, by so doing, ensured complete control over the kingdom. D'Ken then learned that the crystal was too powerful for one person to wield. One consequence is that the various sectors of space are falling to the power of the crystal. 
 
Just before this background is given by Jonath, both the X-Ternals and the Imperial Guard feels a blink in their existence. Jonath explains that this blink is an indication that their part of space is next to fall. The X-Ternals begin to see why the planet would call to them. At this moment, the Imperial Guard attacks; Rictor is with them. Among the fray, Gambit and Guido argue over the use of Lila's powers. Before the fight gets too heated, however, a crystal wave engulfs Jonath's men. The end of Ch'reesharaa begins. Before the X-Ternals are hit, though, they are transported to a ship by the Starjammers, a group led by the former ruler Deathbird. They depart the planet in time to see the entire thing consumed by the crystal wave. Deathbird explains that the M'Kraan Crystal wanted the X-Ternals to see the elimination of that planet in order for the team to fully realize their mission. The message is clear enough and Gambit commits his team to the task of saving the universe from being destroyed.
name: Where No External Has Gone Before!

description:
The Generation Next team led by Colossus and Kitty Pryde attempt to infilitrate the Seattle Core, where Sugar Man runs a child labor camp. Their mission - rescue Colossus' sister Illyana Rasputin.
 
Skin and Chamber hijack a scheduled bus used by the security at the Seattle Core, and kill two guards in the process. Colossus and Shadowcat are surveying the perimeter of the core when an "undercloak", a perimeter guard that hides among the shadows on Sugar Man's orders, nearly kills Shadowcat but is saved by Colossus.
 
Meanwhile, in a downtown spa, Husk, pretending to be human, is "attending" to the needs of a customer called Quietus, the administrator of Core Seattle. After being invited back to Quietus' place, Husk prepares them both a drink and Quietus begins to hit on her. However, Quietus has a device which can detect mutants and discovers that Husk is not who she appears to be. But it is too late as Vincente, having turned into liquid and been drunk by Quietus, returns to solid form and Quietus explodes. Husk and Vincente search through his files for intel on Illyana.
 
Mondo clears the entrance to the core, as Vincente together with Husk disguise themselves as the dead Quietus to gain entrance. Upon entering, and receiving a single from Starsmoore and Skin, they venture further into the core.
 
Deep below in the mining camps, Illyana and Ace survive another day.
name: Hither Comes The Sugar Man

volume.name: The Phantom: The Ghost Who Walks

name: Things Ain't What They Used to Be!

description:
Jean leaves Logan to help human evacuation and arrival to Europe costs, but they meet again at Bristol shore. During evacuation Box and Copycat, who apparently have escaped from the x-men last confrontation, started to attack human civilians including but they are stopped and killed by Jean and Logan. Meanwhile Pierce and the Reavers took advantage of the distraction to camuflage as humans in the crowd so they can leak in humans new territories. The Reavers attacked and took control of one of the main ariships of human resistance responsible of guide system of the human fleet. Weapon X confronted them and managed to apparently stopped the reavers.

At the end Jean leaves definitely Europe planning to warn North Amercia of the preventive attack of Human Council, Weapon X could not stopped her and kissed her.
name: Fire In The Sky!
What If Spider-Man Became a Murderer?

description:
The Apocalypse is about to arrive to the paradise land of Avalon as it is what Destiny saw using her precognition powers. Meanwhile Nightcrawler is travelling in one of the refugee´s submarine but, as expected, nothing would be going easy on him.

Hundreds of lifes at risk and the betrayal of a pirate.
name: X-Calibre, Part 2: Burn

description:
Apocalypse has sent his most trusted assassin (Domino), to track down a unknown telepath with great abilities, he orders to offer him to join his army or die. 
 
The recently adding member of Forge´s outcasts, Essex aka Sinister in disguise, has been testing Nate´s powers, he convinced the team to look up and  destroy one of the Apocalypse´s most secret factories on America. 
 
Nate wants to find himself but with Forge and Essex meddling, he wont be able to discover his true potential...
name: Choosing Sides

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: In case you haven't heard, it's a boy! But there's no time for a shower: in case Rocket and (Buck) Icon heven't heard, Oblivion is here, and he's ready to kill!
name: Approaching Oblivion

description: Part 5 of the 6-part 'School of Anguish.' It's do or die for Xombi and Rabbi Sinnowitz as they enter their final and bloodiest confrontation with the Beli Mah.
name: Reconfigured Angel

description:
SOHAN the boy who was kidnapped by Mantricker seeks toe eradicate the Wolfriders from the world of two moons.
Bearclaw meets Demontricker and reveals his utter contempt for all humans after the accidental death of Mantricker.
name: OF THE FATHERS

description:
Tyleet who is recognised to Scouter speaks with Leetah and Ember about recognition. The story of the births of Dart and Windkin are reminisced, being two children born of formerly recognised couples: Strongbow & Moonshade, and Dewshine & Tyldak. Pike claims he is recognised to dreamberries.
Pike at a fireside-council mentions a few Wolfriders who had previously not been introduced in any of the original ElfQuest by Wendy Pini. These are "Whistlebranch whose delicate piping would calm his chief no matter how hot Mantricker raged.", "Raven's Hair who was black of hair and blacker of humor", and "Moss - you could always find him sleeping in the coolest shade".
Pike tells the story of Hummer, one of the long lost wolfriders who as a girl befriended a red-gold hummingbird. Buckthorn was her peer and closest competitor, who lost to Hummer in seven-out-of-every-eight contests. Finally, the couple had a staring contest, wherein the third discovered each others soul names in the art of recognition, "Wirr, and Prye".
name: WHEN HEAD MEETS HEAD

description: Tamia Korhat and Kullyn Kenn are together on a mission to investigate an asteroid. The Neverending have built a secret dungeon in this particular asteroid and have guarded the entrance with ninja-drone bots. KKullyn Kenn is knocked out, and in his dream he sees Jink communing with the King of The Neverending. He wakes up inside a prison cell, but since the never ending are trying to make a show of peace to the humans, they happily return the "tweak" as a sign of good will.
name: SOUL MEETS SOUL

description:
Guest-starring the Silver Surfer of the 31st Century! On a quest to find his parents, Starhawk discovers Silver Surfer (now known as The Keeper) -- lingering at death's door! When Starhawk is granted custody of the Q-Bands, he learns that they once belonged to his true father -- whose identity will shock you!

Plus: new solo adventures start this month!

First up: Nikki discovers her feelings for an old friend!
name: Orphan In The Storm
Domitian Over All

description: The Arnorines are put through intense training before their next secret mission: protect Cuban Dictator Fidel Castro from enemy guerrilla fighters. How will the Armorines grapple with being called on to defendone of their nation's oldest enemies?
name: The Cuban Connection, Part 1 - Maneuvers

description:
1. Minds Part 7

Dave appears to Cerebus in his head. Also what happened to jaka is shown.

2. Bacchus preview (By Eddie Campbell)
name: Mothers and Daughters 43 : Minds Part 7

description:
Aquaman becomes trapped between two warring elemental entities: Corona, the new fire elemental, and the water elemental Naiad.

The issue kicks off with Corona now set on killing all of the Deep Six for their destruction of her village, and then her deciding to destroy the village herself following her destruction of the Six. While Dolphin, Aquaman, and Koryak continue to battle the remaining members of the Six in the cave. Aqualad is still captured, as Letfios begs for his life from the flesh eating water, trying to free himself as the water descends on him.

The terrified Six then beg Aquaman to save them from Corona in exchange for their leaving of Earth and never returning. Aquaman then attempts to talk her out of murder while they open a boom tube escaping her,leading her to personally blame Aquaman and attack him. Aquaman is then saved by Koryak, until the arrival of Naiad who has set out to eliminate Corona for being a tainted elemental.Koryak then manages attempts to use his hard water abilities to spin Naiads body to pieces as a distraction, so they can flee which ultimately fails. Aquaman then attempts to appeal to Naiad by pledging to help her, by asking Kako to kill him so she can be free of the anger repressed inside of her. Ultimately Naiad sees the humanity still inside of Corona, and decides to spare her so they can act as a balance for another, as she leaves with her fellow elemental.

In Poseidonis Vulko and several other scientists try to discover what has raised the city up, with Vulko believing it to be something trying to push it's way up.
name: Elemental, My Dear Aquaman

description: Criminals, Part 2 of 2. Batman finds his undercover prison search suddenly derailed. The warden's life is now in the inmates' bargaining chip, and the only way the Dark Knight can save him is by allowing himself to be unmasked.
name: Criminals Part 2

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

name: Streets of Fire, Hearts of Rage
Students

description: In this unlucky 13th issue (unlucky for X, that is), "The War for Arcadia" witnesses its most unexpected casualty yet -- X himself! Nothing will be the same in Arcadia after this landmark issue!
name: Wipeout!

description:
Catwoman is hired by movie producer Carlos Weinberg to acquire the screenplay to Matt Achenbach's next movie. Achenbach's last five pictures broke the hundred millions mark. Weinberg is planning on beating him to video and overseas fastplay. Only problem is, he has got the only copy of the script and the movie is shooting now. It is not based on a novel or a treatment. It is all out of his head.

Then there is the hurricane and the Lurker, the only too real monster of the movie...
name: More Edge, More Heart

description:
Overview

Look! Down in the sewers! It's a rat! It's a cave! It's giant cyborg alligators! Babe descends into the muck-encrusted world of the flushed and forgotten to catch the sinister Shrewmanoid and his malodorous mutants! Will she stop them from carrying out their evil plan du jour, or will she become an appetizer for the alligators?! It's Byrne at his best: fantastic, fun, and furious! Featuring a special guest appearance by Abe Sapien of Hellboy, and a final page guaranteed to surprise, delight, and confuse fans everywhere!
Violence and the music of a mysterious street musician draw the Dark Knight into the underground world of Gotham City's jazz scene, where legendary musician Blue Byrd seems to have come back to life.
name: Brothers of the Bop

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight: Jazz

description: As The Joker begins kidnapping various people throughout the city, Dr. Arkham turns to a man known only as Mr. Wild.  The Batman meanwhile starts his own investigation and soon comes in contact with Joker's Gang.  Meanwhile Jim Gordon and Sarah Essen visit Harvey Bullock in the hospital through some intense tension.  As The Joker's gang gets away they leave a man behind, prompting Mr. Wild to interrogate him, but how far will he go?  and just who is Mr. Wild?
name: Falls Upon The Joker: Part One: The King of Comedy

description: Anima’s father Dwight Mason has become the Shrike, a bird of vengeance, and he is stalking drug dealers in Chicago. Anima and Hawkman fight the Shrike, but Anima refuses to deliver the killing blow, allowing the Shrike to escape. Meanwhile, Anima’s friend Dred’s cousin Ramsey is looking to get revenge on the death of Dred’s brother. Ramsey’s gang has gotten word from some corrupt police officers where the murderer, Dwayne, is being transported to and when. As Ramsey prepares to kill Dwayne, Anima and Hawkman continue to hunt for the Shrike. Hawkman finds Shrike first, and talks Dwight into controlling the beast. Anima finds out about Ramsey’s plan, and stops him before he kills. The four come together, where Ramsey turns a new leaf and Dwight continues to hone the Shrike as a force for good.
name: Harvest

description:
Leviathan embarks on a mission of vengeance, taking the Legion's most powerful members with him and leaving the rest of the team shorthanded.

Leviathan assembles the most powerful Legionnaires on a mission of revenge to take down Tangleweb, who had previously killed Legionnaire Kid Quantum. Invisible Kid is offended by being left off the mission and decides to find his own way after the team. Back on Earth, a Legionnaire is brutally attacked by members of the xenophobic White Triangle.
name: Insect Fear

description:
Deathtrap ups the ante against Superman and Mister Miracle with increasingly deadly snares, as the first evidence appears that someone with evil designs has learned the Man of Steel's true identity.

Notes:

  • Triangle 1995 #13.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #708.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #99.
name: - - Deathtrap!

description: Final issue. Part 4 of 4. It's Etrigan's infernal series finale when the Demon enters the final battle with Karrien Excalibris, the Archangel of War.

In the late 1800s the Eternal Warrior confronts his son, a madman out to kill and destroy. Vowing to stop his son from wreaking more havoc Gilad tracks him down in the modern day.

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".

1st appearances:

- Durant

- Jack The Ripper
name: Mortal Kin - Part 1: Sharper Than A Serpent's Tooth

description:
Strange visions of his cousin, Zorn, have Clay on edge. What can these vision mean and could Samantha be in trouble? Will the Geomancer have to face Zorn once again?

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".
name: Desert Storm

description: While Magnus and Leeja have to be apart, Leeja is kidnapped by a pair of robots who claim to be with a robotic right to life alliance which starts making requests for robots in “Cold Blooded.”
name: Cold Blooded

description:
"The Cliff Men" originally presented in Turok Son Of Stone #24, June-Aug 1961.
"Terror of the Bog" originally presented in Turok Son Of Stone #33, June 1963.

Cover Gallery (original covers):
Issue #596 (#1), December 1954
Issue #656 (#2), October 1955
Issue #7, May 1957
Issue #9, September-November 1957
name: The Cliff Men; Terror Of The Bog

volume.name: The Original Turok, Son of Stone

name: Steel, Meat, & Potatoes - Part One

description: While in captivity, Turok is forced to engage in battle and then finds himself caught between old enemies, bounty hunters and the law and he then makes a decision that will change his life.
name: Mystery Wheel

description:
Overview

America's Melting Pot is boiling over, and Colors in Black is cleaning up the mess. In this third issue we catch three more views from the front lines of the race wars. "Just Like Rooster"tells the story of three little boys and their misplaced idolatry for a local dealer/pimp. In "Front Bar for a Drink and a Smoke," a young man learns the value of racial relations... firsthand. Finally, "The Back of the Bus" takes a look at the modern state of one of the most critical symbols of civil rights in America... the back of the bus.

The revolution will not be televised... It will be illustrated.

Gas up your tank and start up your engine! We're revving on a rally towards DHP #100! First stop is the Far East, where we'll devour a "Pot Full of Noodles" with The Kabuki Kid! It's your standard fare of samurai/cowboy satires, cooked up courtesy of mssrs. Rennie and Langridge! But don't fill up too much, 'cause you'll need to be lean and mean to follow Hal in "Here and Now." Ed Brubaker and Stefano Gaudiano have sent private dick Hal on the wildest investigation of them all: that of his own past! Then it's on to "The Picture of Doreen Grey," by Vertigo creator Eddie Campbell. He's got The Eyeball Kid running for the garter, when Big Ginny, Queen of the Amazons, plunges into them sacred nuptials with Joe Theseus! All in all, it's a rousing start in the big ride to the magnificent #100!

Han Solo and Princess Leia have taken refuge with their twins on the planet New Alderaan. But refuge, it seems, eludes the family when Emperor Palpatine and an AT-AT battalion come hunting for Rebel officers. Worry not, Leia! They don't want your lives... they just want your children!
name: Hand of Darkness

description: Artoo-Detoo and See-Threepio may have bitten off more than they can chew! Their boss has been blown to bits, and they're marooned in perhaps the most dangerous place in the universe: Nar Shaddaa! The beautiful and deadly Jace Forno has somehow wormed her mercenary self into the spaceport's top security position, and it seems like she's got an agenda for taking care of all kinds of meddlesome droids!
name: Rebellion, Part 2 of 4

description: In "Watchdogged Wolf," Wolfy spots Red on the beach and tries to steal a kiss. However, Red's bodyguard -- a vicious bulldog named "Fluffy" -- comes to Red's defense and takes a bite out of crime! In "Tastes Like Chicken," Meathead the dog starts a new job at a fast-food joint. But when Screwball Squirrel steps in as Meathead's co-worker, things run amok -- and Meathead probably won't have his job much longer!
name: Watchdogged Wolf; Taste Like Chicken

description:
Part 2 of the 7-part 'The Death of Clark Kent.' With those close to Clark Kent in mortal danger from the villain who's discovered his double identity, Superman becomes torn between protecting his parents and checking on Lois. And when the Man of Steel tries to contact her...there's no answer.

Conduit goes after Clark Kent's parents.

Notes:

  • Twinkles is a parody of Twinkies.
  • Last $1.50 issue.
  • Last paper and color format used. The next issue uses heavier stock paper and glossy pages.
  • Triangle 1995 #19.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #100.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #710.
name: The Hit!

description: Part 3 of the 3-part 'Wild Type': A "Monkey Trial" the likes of which the world has never seen occurs when Animal Man stops a mob from killing some baboons believed to have murdered three hunters.
name: Money Trial [Wild Type Part 3]

description: As a gang murders innocent Gotham City citizens, the deadly Black Spider battles the Dark Knight.
name: Black Mask: The Spidered Face

description:
The return of Firestorm, The Nuclear Man! Ronald Raymond inexplicably goes meta again, just as the Justice League gains control of Mount Thunder and secures it as its new base of operations.

With Mount Thunder secure, the Extreme Justice team now has some down time. Blue Beetle begins examining Amazing-Man’s powers, while Maxima confronts Captain Atom about their past. Captain Atom reveals that he has promised himself to Plastique, which angers Maxima. Maxima flees, using debris from Mount Thunder to fashion a nearby base of her own. The team decides to give Maxima some room, deciding to look into a brewing Crisis in Pittsburgh. They find that something has triggered Ronnie Raymond’s powers again, and he is aflame flying high above the city. The team investigates, and is brought up-to-speed by Oberon and Skeets. Amazing-Man manages to absorb some of Firestorm’s energy, while the rest of the team calms him down. Once back in control, Ronnie receives a mental message from Martin Stein, the elemental Firestorm last seen exploring the galaxy. Martin reveals that he is heading home.
name: The Brave and the Crazy

description: Drawn to Hollywood in their pursuit of malevolent mystic forces, Fate and Holly learn the terrible truth behind the menace of the Dark Agent: he gets 10%-of everything. Plus, Qabala returns from his earlier defeat at Fate's hands…with demonic presences that need to be fed.
name: A Hell of A Town

description: Wally copes with his new Speed Force powers, such as the ability to share speed. Also Iris tells Wally she must return to the future.
name: Going the Distance

description:
Kyle Rayner faces his toughest challenge yet. If the neophyte Green Lantern can't find a way to defeat the mechanical monstrosity known as Duality he may loose his ring forever.

Kyle and Donna take a jog through New York and Kyle is having a hard time keeping up with the superior athletics of a longtime superhero, Titan and Amazon princess now turned Darkstar. Kyle begs her to stop, once they do they get mugged, Kyle uses his ring while Donna uses martial arts she then demonstrates to Kyle how to defend himself without the ring. He is impressed.

He offers her the cartridge ride he promised a few issues back. She has to cut though so he transforms and flies across New York then gets attacked by a monster. Kyle fights valiantly but the monster wins. Back at his apartment Ganthet reveals he sent the monster, he then tells Kyle the origins of the ring before asking him to hand it back. Kyle refuses and just then Hal Jordan walks in.
name: Ganthet's Tale Redux

description: Paul Jenkins begins his HELLBLAZER run with ""Dreamtime"" part 1! John Constantine plunges deep into an arcane landscape, where a powerful entity known as the Rainbow Serpent intends to punish man's treatment of the environment by clearing the earth of all animal life.
name: Dreamtime

description: Bart attacks Wally, while Linda gets attacked by some of Kobra's men, she is saved by Argus and Hartley Rathaway (the reformed Pied Piper). Wally brings Bart to where Iris is staying,and Bart, recognizing his grandma, calms down. But then, one of Kobra's men appear and then disappear, leaving a message that he will kill them all if Linda continues her research into the Kobra "cult". Bart goes to attack him just as the man disappears, but Bart went with him.
name: Crossfire

description: Jonah's new friends simply want to play their music. But human gunslingers and flesh-crazed monsters have other plans.

volume.name: Jonah Hex: Riders of the Worm and Such

description: A search for Gypsy and the Ray leads Triumph and Despero to an ancient vampire with links to Gypsy's past...and who may be responsible for the deaths of two Task Force heroes.

While Jesse learns more about his new powers, the Saint of Killers cuts a bloody swath through Sheriff Hugo Root's men. But that's nothing compared to the horror of Root's home life, or Cassidy's vampire appetites.

Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy are on the run from The Saint; we meet Sheriff Root's disfigured son; Cassidy's true nature is revealed!
name: And Hell Followed with Him

description: As the Butcher's insatiable appetite continues unabated, the Golden Age Sandman's dreams become violent nightmares.
name: Night of the Butcher: Act 2 of 4

description: A strange twist of fate results in hideous consequences that will affect the future of the Dreaming forever! "The Kindly Ones" part 12.
name: The Kindly Ones, Part 12

description: Part 1 of the 5-part 'Nasty Infections.' A grotesquely virulent sickness spreads through Shade's home, causing widespread dementia, decay...and death.
name: Nasty Infections, Part One: Grotesquery

description: A Wolf in Cheap Clothing, Part 3 of 4. The mystery on the Klingon frontier world deepens as Kirk encounters an old 'friend' from Starfleet Academy and learns of a secret mission gone terribly wrong.
name: A Wolf...In Cheap Clothing Part Three

description: Part 1 of 5. The Federation's fragile peace with the Tholians is shattered when Klingon and Federation outposts are destroyed. But the U.S.S. Enterprise soon learns that a force far more sinister is behind the attacks - something before which they are all...irrelevant.
name: War and Madness Part I:The First Casualty
